items.title: Astros win 5th straight thanks to arms, Altuve
items.summary: Collin McHugh won his third consecutive decision and combined with four relievers to handcuff the White Sox and send the American League West-champion Astros to their fifth win a row, 3-1, in Tuesday night's series opener at Minute Maid Park.

items.title: Dodgers fall to Phils; magic number stays 3
items.summary: The magic number for a fifth consecutive National League West title stubbornly remained at three for the Dodgers on Tuesday night, as Rhys Hoskins' three-run double and four RBIs rallied the Phillies to a 6-2 win at Citizens Bank Park.

items.title: Fowler's clutch hits boost Cards in needed win
items.summary: Trying to hang on to their quickly fading postseason hopes, the Cardinals needed an early comeback then some late clutch hitting. It added up to an 8-6 victory over the Reds in 10 innings on Tuesday night at Great American Ball Park.

items.title: Realmuto hits walk-off HR in wild win over Mets
items.summary: The Marlins aren't going down quietly in the National League Wild Card chase. After being an out away from elimination on Tuesday night, J.T. Realmuto delivered a walk-off home run in the 10th inning that lifted Miami to a 5-4 win over the Mets at Marlins Park.
